defaultWritten evidence from Sherborne Transport Action Group (TIC 107)
default&#xa0;
defaultThe Sherborne Transport Action Group (STAG) aims to improve transport provision for the people of Sherborne and the surrounding villages, particularly to help those 
defaultwithout access to a car and to encourage car owners to use other modes.
default&#xa0;
defaultSTAG welcomes all who have an interest in its objects.  Members may include representatives of town and parish councils, transport-related organisations, transport-providers and other
default interested members of the community.
default&#xa0;
defaultThis submission was agreed by STAG at its meeting on 19 September 2013.default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
defaultThe great majority of enquiries into local transport have concentrated almost wholly on the context of cities and large towns.  We welcome the 
defaultemphasis of the current enquiry .  We hope, however, that it will include not only areas which are truly isolated, but also the rural areas which cannot be regarded as isolated, but where the dispersal of population raises issues entirely different from th
defaultose of the large urban areas.  Sherborne
default,
default with a population of 10,000 and surrounding villages
default of a few hundred, 
defaultcome
defaults
default firmly in this category.
default 
default&#xa0;
default1.  defaultHow do Government and local authorities identify demand for passenger transport in isolated communities (idefaultncluding rural and urban areas and island communities)?default2.  defaultTo what extent are the needs of different groups of passengers (defaulte.g. people with disabilities, older people, young people) taken into account in determining the provision of public transport to isolated communities?default3.  defaultWhat are the main challenges associated with providing better and more consistent bus and rail services to isolated defaultcommunities? How can these challenges be overcome?default4.  defaultHow effectively do Community Trdefaultansport services address the needs of passengers in isolated communities? How could Community Transport be improved?default&#xa0;
default5.  defaultTo what extent should passengers in isolated communities be expected to rely on defaulttaxis and other demand-responsive transport services?default6.  defaultWhat are the main challenges associated with funding transport services in isdefaultolated communities? How can these services be made more affordable?default&#xa0;
